A certificate of authorization shall set forth:
The foreign entity's real name and, if applicable, its fictitious name as adopted for use in this Commonwealth;
That the foreign entity is authorized to transact business in this Commonwealth;
That all fees, taxes, and penalties owed to this Commonwealth have been paid, if:
Payment is reflected in the records of the Secretary of State; and
Nonpayment affects the authorization of the foreign entity to transact business in this Commonwealth;
That its most recent annual report required by KRS 14A.6-010 or predecessor law has been filed by the Secretary of State;
That no certificate of withdrawal or document of similar import under prior law has been filed; and
Other facts of record in the office of the Secretary of State that may be requested by the applicant.
